A plugin (or JIRA) cannot yet prevent a user from deleting special issue types. When issue types are deleted, JIRA allows the ID to be re-used for another issue type when it is subsequently created.

This causes problems for plugins like GreenHopper, because we store these IDs for special use and are then not notified when they are no longer valid.

If the backup created for a JIRA import causes both the following warnings:
{panel}The attachment path /path/in/backup specified in the backup file is not valid.{panel}
and
{panel}You are attempting to import data from JIRA 6.0-OD-07.2 which is a more recent version than this version. Some features that you may have used before will not be available in this version of JIRA. Click here to acknowledge this error and proceed anyway.{panel}

The user will never be able to continue. When one is acknowledged the import will attempt to continue but then show the other error. Acknowledging the second error results in the first being shown again. This will go on indefinitely, meaning the user must edit the {{entities.xml}} to get rid of the path error.

