This is something we run into all the time: issues resolved with 'Current' in the fix version. With Greenhopper nested versions, this has a bad side-effect. When 'Current' is moved from a sub-version of 2.0 to 2.1, for example, all of the issues fixed in 'Current' move with it, which messes up the ability to see what was actually fixed in 2.0.

Instead of relying on each developer to remember to remove 'Current' from the fix version, it would be nice if this could be enforced by the workflow, either with a post function that automatically removes it or a validator that won't let you resolve until you do.

This seems like it could be generally useful if we allow the list of disallowed fix versions to be configurable.

